The marchers first gathered at Church Square and then made their way to Union Buildings where they were addressed by various leaders of political parties. Tens of thousands of people took to the streets of Pretoria, all with a common purpose - to show their discontent with President Zuma as leader of South Africa.The marchers first gathered at Church Square and then made their way to Union Buildings where they were addressed by various leaders of political parties.Protesters wearing different T-shirt all gathered and marched together for &quot;a government governed for the people by the people&quot;.